> I need to be able to asynchronously get data from all kinds of places before I can even think about calling React.renderToString<p>You can define middlewares, as you would do server-side with expressjs:<p><pre><code>    router.route({
      method: &#x27;GET&#x27;,
      path: &#x27;/users/:userId&#x27;,
      handler: function (ctx) {
        // load user async
        getUser(ctx.params.userId, function (err, user) {
          ctx.user = user;
          ctx.next(); // exec next middleware
        }); 
      }
    });
</code></pre>
There is a `demo` folder with a detailed example. The main entry point for the client is here <a href="https://github.com/gcanti/tom/blob/master/demo/client.js#L21" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/gcanti/tom/blob/master/demo/client.js#L21</a>
